defs.name: Complex
defs.docs: A complex number in Cartesian form.

defs.name: re
defs.docs: Real portion of the complex number

defs.name: im
defs.docs: Imaginary portion of the complex number

defs.name: norm_sqr
defs.docs:
Returns the square of the norm (since `T` doesn't necessarily
 have a sqrt function), i.e. `re^2 + im^2`.

defs.name: powu
defs.docs: Raises `self` to an unsigned integer power.

defs.name: conj
defs.docs: Returns the complex conjugate. i.e. `re - i im`

defs.name: powi
defs.docs: Raises `self` to a signed integer power.

defs.name: l1_norm
defs.docs: Returns the L1 norm `|re| + |im|` -- the [Manhattan distance] from the origin.

defs.name: is_nan
defs.docs: Checks if the given complex number is NaN

defs.name: is_infinite
defs.docs: Checks if the given complex number is infinite

defs.name: is_finite
defs.docs: Checks if the given complex number is finite

defs.name: is_normal
defs.docs: Checks if the given complex number is normal
